#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:3
msgid "The Text Editor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:5
msgid ""
"Blender has a :guilabel:`Text Editor` among its windows types, accessible "
"via the :guilabel:`Text Editor` button ("
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:9
msgid ") of the :guilabel:`Window type` menu, or via :kbd:`shift-f11`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:11
msgid ""
"The newly opened Text window is grey and empty, with a very simple toolbar "
"(*Text Toolbar*)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:16
msgid "Text Toolbar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:19
msgid ""
"From left to right there are the standard :guilabel:`Window type` selection "
"button and the window menus. Then there is the Text ID Block browse button "
"followed by the New button for creating new Text files. Once you click it, "
"you will find that the Toolbar has changed.. for good!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:29
msgid "Text Toolbar with a file open"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:32
msgid ""
"Now you find a textbox to change name of your text file, followed by **+** "
"button to create new files. To remove the text block, click the **X** "
"button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:36
msgid ""
"The following three buttons toggle display of line numbers, word-wrap text "
"and syntax  highlighting respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:39
msgid ""
"Typing on the keyboard produces text in the text buffer. As usual, pressing "
"dragging and releasing :kbd:`Lmb` selects text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:42
msgid "The following keyboard commands apply:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:44
msgid ":kbd:`ctrl-C` - Copies the marked text into the text clipboard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:45
msgid ":kbd:`ctrl-X` - Cuts out the marked text into the text clipboard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:46
msgid ""
":kbd:`ctrl-V` - Pastes the text from the clipboard at the cursor location in"
" the Text window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:47
msgid ""
":kbd:`shift-ctrl-alt-S` - Saves unsaved text as a text file, a "
":guilabel:`File Browser` window appears."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:48
msgid ":kbd:`alt-S` - Saves an already open file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:49
msgid ""
":kbd:`alt-O` - Loads a text, a :guilabel:`File Browser` window appears."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:50
msgid ":kbd:`alt-P` - Executes the text as a Python script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:51
msgid ":kbd:`ctrl-Z` - Undo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:52
msgid ":kbd:`ctrl-shift-Z` - Redo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:53
msgid ""
":kbd:`alt-R` - Reopen (reloads) the current buffer (all non-saved "
"modifications are lost)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:54
msgid ""
":kbd:`alt-M` - Converts the content of the text window into 3D text (max 100"
" chars)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:56
msgid ""
"To delete a text buffer just press the :guilabel:`X` button next to the "
"buffer's name, just as you do for materials, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:59
msgid ""
"The most notable keystroke is :kbd:`alt-P` which makes the content of the "
"buffer being parsed by the internal Python interpreter built into Blender. "
"The next page will present an example of Python scripting. Before going on "
"it is worth noticing that Blender comes with a fully functional Python "
"interpreter built in, and with a lots of Blender-specific modules, as "
"described in the :doc:`API references </extensions/python/references>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:65
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Text Editor` has now also some dedicated Python scripts, "
"which add some useful writing tools, like a class/function/variable browser,"
" completion... You can access them through the :guilabel:`Text` â†’ "
":guilabel:`Text Plugins` menu entry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:71
msgid "Other usages for the Text window"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/extensions/python/text_editor.rst:73
msgid ""
"The text window is handy also when you want to share your . blend files with"
" the community or with your friends. A Text window can be used to write in a"
" README text explaining the contents of your blender file. Much more handy "
"than having it on a separate application. Be sure to keep it visible when "
"saving! If you are sharing the file with the community and you want to share"
" it under some license you can write the license in a text window."
msgstr ""

